==Onmyoji==
{{Short description|Japanese court diviner position}}
{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2021}}
{{Other uses|Onmyoji (disambiguation)}}[[File:Tamamonomae_Onmyoji.jpg|right|thumb|300x300px|From the Nara picture book "[[Tamamo-no-Mae]]," published in the early [[Edo period]], depicting an onmyōji performing divination with [[counting rods]]. From the collection of the [[Kyoto University]] Library.]]


In general, the [[List of Japanese court ranks, positions and hereditary titles|court rank]] of the technical officers in each ministry was set low, but the rank of the technical officers in the Bureau of Onmyō was set higher than that of the technical officers in other ministries. However, since the Bureau of Onmyō was an internal bureau of the Ministry of Center, the rank of the fourth grade administrative officials was naturally lower than that of the main ministry, and only a Head of Onmyō allowed to ascend to the hall of the [[Kyoto Imperial Palace|Seiryōden]], the place of daily life of the [[Emperor of Japan|Emperor]], to {{ill|Temmon missō|lt=report directly|ja|天文密奏}}.
